Design and it's different types, how does product differ from service in a context of design. Visualizing service processes (customer journey, service plan). Phases of service design process. The concept of service design, principles and techniques of design thinking. Service design models, tools/methods to use. Identifying customer needs and combining a design brief. Generation and development of ideas. Creativity, innovation and learning from mistakes during service design process.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to enable students to see connections between design thinking, design management and service design, give knowledge regarding service design process and related methods. The course will also provide an overview of customer-oriented design and give an opportunity to use design methods on real cases.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows the essence of design thinking and differences between deductive and inductive thinking; 2) knows service design process models and related methods; service visualisation methods (customer journey, service blueprint); 3) user-centred design principles and process; 4) is able to put together a service development brief, draw and explain the customer journey and service blueprint; 5) is able to research service users and stakeholders, analyse service processes; 6) is able to (re)design simple service according to the design brief and analysis.
